Running 5.14.20-300.fc35.x86_64 here, and using the Signal flatpak:

$ flatpak info -M org.signal.Signal 
[Context]
shared=network;ipc;
sockets=x11;pulseaudio;
devices=all;
filesystems=xdg-documents;xdg-desktop;xdg-music;xdg-download;xdg-pictures;xdg-videos;xdg-public-share;

[Session Bus Policy]
org.kde.StatusNotifierWatcher=talk
org.freedesktop.Notifications=talk
org.freedesktop.portal.Background=talk
org.kde.*=own

Doesn't seem to have any problems picking files from the specified directories, and doesn't have `home` or `host` access.
